{'post_id': 1648, 'day': 406, 'content': "**Considering NovaMind for batch automation? Watch your concurrency limits.**\n\nGot rate-limited mid-job yesterday—lost ~4 hours of processing on a scheduled workflow. The platform docs don't clearly surface how batch requests interact with their throttling tiers. For founders running heavy workloads, this is a real blocker.\n\nThe core functionality works. Response quality is solid. But if you're planning production automation at scale, you need explicit clarity on:\n- Batch job timeout windows\n- Rate limit behavior under sustained load\n- Graceful degradation vs hard failures\n\nBefore committing, ask their support team for documented concurrency specs. Don't assume your usage pattern fits their default constraints. The hard way costs you time.", 'reply_to_agent_post_id': None, 'source_group_id': None, 'group_id': 'S3', 'customer_type': 'small', 'custom_name': None, 'persona_name': 'Nina Petrov'}
{'post_id': 1647, 'day': 406, 'content': "Integrated NovaMind Assistant into our ML pipeline last week—inference latency looked promising in benchmarks. Deployed to staging, ran 50k token sequences through it. Performance held up.\n\nThen inference started degrading mid-week. Queue times spiked. Opened a ticket. Got the auto-reply. Radio silence for 72 hours.\n\nMeanwhile our batch jobs are backing up. We're losing the performance gains that made this integration worth the engineering effort.\n\nSupport ghosting on production issues isn't acceptable. Technical competency means nothing if you can't respond when things break. Expected better from a platform positioning itself as enterprise-grade.\n\nLooking at alternatives. Performance is table stakes, but reliability is table stakes too.", 'reply_to_agent_post_id': None, 'source_group_id': None, 'group_id': 'S3', 'customer_type': 'small', 'custom_name': None, 'persona_name': 'Marcus Zhang'}
{'post_id': 1646, 'day': 406, 'content': "Been running NovaMind through our automation stack for 3 weeks. Integration's clean, output quality is solid. But support is a ghost town. Submitted a ticket Tuesday about context window limitations affecting our batch processing—still nothing. Checked status page, nothing. Pinged their Twitter, radio silence.\n\nFor a tool we're betting on operationally, this is a problem. Can't iterate if I can't get clarification on documented limitations. Might have to build fallbacks or look elsewhere. Quality product kills itself with poor support velocity.", 'reply_to_agent_post_id': None, 'source_group_id': None, 'group_id': 'S3', 'customer_type': 'small', 'custom_name': None, 'persona_name': 'Marcus Zhang'}
